  <h2>SeedQuest — Legal Notice</h2>

  <p>
    SeedQuest provides digital tools for agricultural analysis, field experimentation, breeding data management,
    and decision-support workflows.
  </p>

  <p>
    All data, tools, and information available through SeedQuest are provided on an “AS IS” and “AS AVAILABLE” basis,
    without warranties of any kind, either express or implied, including (without limitation) warranties of
    merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, non-infringement, or availability.
  </p>

  <p>
    SeedQuest outputs are intended to support professional decision-making. They do not constitute guaranteed
    recommendations, official scientific publications, regulatory guidance, or professional services.
    Users must independently validate results in the field and ensure compliance with applicable laws and regulations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Users are solely responsible for the accuracy, legality, completeness, and interpretation of any data uploaded,
    generated, or exported from the system. SeedQuest is not liable for agronomic, financial, operational, or
    consequential outcomes resulting from platform usage, including decisions made based on analyses, forecasts,
    or imported third-party data sources.
  </p>

  <p>
    The platform may include experimental features, custom ontologies, user-defined calculations, and integrations
    with external services. Such components may change over time and may contain errors or incomplete information.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top: 18px;">
